  <!-- SPRINT PROCESS -->
  <div class="intermediary-title">
    <h4 class="text-left">SPRINT PROCESS</h4>
    <p></p>
  </div>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="process">
      <div class="steps col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-4 text-center">
        <div class="step-title">GENERAL</div>
        <p class="step-content text-left">This list is used to gather all the info that concerns the development team and the sprint in general.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="steps col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-4 text-center">
        <div class="step-title">USER STORIES</div>
        <p class="step-content text-left">
          This list gathers all users stories that are going to be implemented during the sprint. Depending on the number of team members, a Sprint shouldn't have more than 10 user stories.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="steps col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-4 text-center">
        <div class="step-title">BACKLOG</div>
        <p class="step-content text-left">This list contains all sub-tasks that need to be done in order to develop all user stories planned for the Sprint. The Product Owner assigns each task to a team contributor, and gives it a T-shirt size (see below) depending on the difficulty.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="steps col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-4 text-center">
        <div class="step-title">DOING</div>
        <div class="step-content text-left">
          <p>Each time a member of the team is working on a new development, they take a card from the backlog and put it on this list. When finished, they move the card from this list to the next.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="steps col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-4 text-center">
        <div class="step-title">READY FOR REVIEW</div>
        <p class="step-content text-left">Great product owners makes sure each line of code is reviwed by a second pair of eyes. This is the list of items waiting for review, usually by a senior dev.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="steps col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-4 text-center">
        <div class="step-title">REVIEWING</div>
        <p class="step-content text-left">Code in review is placed on this list. Adjustments and improvements are made both by the reviewer and the reviewee.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="steps col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-4 text-center">
        <div class="step-title">DONE</div>
        <p class="step-content text-left">When a task is finished and reviwed, it is put on this list.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="steps col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-4 text-center">
        <div class="step-title">DEPLOYED</div>
        <p class="step-content text-left">Every x days, the completed new features are deployed in a demo or production environment.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
